title: Paterson rapper Fetty Wap nominated for two American Music Awards
text:
Paterson rapper Fetty Wap nominated for two American Music Awards October 13, 2015, 11:46 AM Last updated: Tuesday, October 13, 2015, 11:50 AM Associated Press Buy this photo MICHAEL KARAS/STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER Fetty Wap performs at Bauerle Field at his free concert for Paterson school students on Thursday, Aug. 27, 2015. 
Paterson rapper Fetty Wap received two American Music Awards nominations Tuesday. 
The 25-year-old newcomer was nominated for New Artist Of The Year and Favorite Artist – Rap/Hip-Hop, competing against Drake and Nicki Minaj in the latter category. 
Taylor Swift earned six nominations, and if she wins them all, the singer will become the most-honored artist in the show’s history. Ed Sheeran and the Weeknd had five nominations each — neither has won before. 
Swift was one of 10 nominees for artist of the year. She’s won 16 American Music Awards. Whitney Houston is the most-honored artist in the award show’s history, with 21 wins. 
Jennifer Lopez will host the show, which will air Nov. 22 from Los Angeles on ABC.
